      "1. Gate 3 + AC-2: context-chain bug in RunParallel — phaseCtx, phaseCancel = context.WithCancel(phaseCtx) at parallel.go:110 causes each phase's context to be derived from the previous phase's cancelled context. After phase 0 completes and phaseCancel() is called, phase 1's context is immediately cancelled. Dependent tracks in phase 1+ are skipped (\"depends_on failed (phase barrier)\") even when their dependencies PASS. Verified: T1 passes → T2 (depends_on T1) is SKIPPED. Fix: use context.WithCancel(ctx) instead of context.WithCancel(phaseCtx) at parallel.go:110.",
